JOHANNESBURG - A light aircraft that crashed near Nasrec, south of Johannesburg on Sunday morning was a training flight carrying two passengers. The South African Civil Aviation Authority (Sacca) said both occupants died on the scene. The aircraft crashed close to a mine dump near the FNB stadium, on a round trip from Grand Central Airport in Midrand. Sacca spokesperson Sisa Majola said a preliminary report would be released in the next 30 days. "The accident and incidents division has been informed of an aircraft accident that occurred this morning Sunday the 15th of January at approximately 9 o'clock local time. Onboard the aircraft where two occupants who both sustained fatal injuries. The aircraft itself sustained substantial damage," said Majola.